Like several other popular garden flowers, nicotianas (also known as tobacco flower) have evolved very different flowers to suit different pollinators. Pale-coloured flowers, often with long petal tubes and a strong scent, are pollinated by various hawkmoths. But nicotianas are from the warmer parts of the United States, and many species have evolved to be pollinated by hummingbirds. These species typically have red flowers with a shorter tube, and no scent.
